original: Magnusson, Albin Dag Ingemar, advokat, Göteborg, f. 31/7/09 i Gbg av Niils Albin M. o. Tora Stenberg. G. 37 m. Ingeborg Forshell Barn: Dag-Björn f. 39, Karin Elisabeth 41, Oiof Anders 42, Ingeborg Margareta 47. — Stud:ex. v. Gbgs h. latin 29, jur. kand. i Sthlm 34. Tingstjg. i Inlands doms. 34-37, egen adv:verksamh. i Gbg sed. 37. Led. av Sv:es adv:samf. sed. 39.
translated: Magnusson, Albin Dag Ingemar, lawyer, Gothenburg, b. 31/7/09 in Gothenburg to Niils Albin M. and Tora Stenberg. Married in 1937 to Ingeborg Forshell. Children: Dag-Björn b. 1939, Karin Elisabeth b. 1941, Oiof Anders b. 1942, Ingeborg Margareta b. 1947. Completed secondary school at Gothenburg's Latin School in 1929, graduated with a law degree in Stockholm in 1934. Served as a court clerk in the Inlands district court from 1934 to 1937, started his own law practice in Gothenburg in 1937. Became a member of the Swedish Bar Association in 1939.
